adat=tradition, old customs, traditional law
akhirnya=finally, at last, lastly, in the end
berkunjung (ke)=to make a visit (to)
indah=beautiful (when talking about natural scenery, art, parts of the body, but not someone's overally appearance)
katanya=I've heard that..., people say..., they say...
kuat=strong
menarik=interesting, attractive
menurut=according to...
perjalanan=a trip, a journey, travel
pertama-tama=firstly, first of all
propinsi=a province
rencana=a plan
bensin=petrol
